The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                Three persons were injured after the boundary wall of the closed Noor Mahal cinema near the Park Street-Mullickbazar crossing fell following heavy rainfall on Sunday morning. Police said the injured were taken to National Medical College and Hospital where the condition of 62-year-old Aminul Haque, a cook at a hotel near the hall, was stated to be critical. The other two were released after first-aid.    Namrata Sarkar, a 23-year-old housewife, was found hanging in her in-laws house in Baguiati on Sunday morning. Husband Pijush and her parents were arrested following a complaint by Namratas father, a resident of Balurghat, that the trio had subjected her to mental and physical torture. Pijush, an electrical engineer in an IT company, and Namrata married 18 months ago. A preliminary probe revealed that the couple had fought over Pijushs smoking habit.    A woman in her mid-30s died after being run over by a train near Bidhannagar Road station on Sunday afternoon. An infant girl the woman was carrying was injured. The girl was handed over to an NGO, police said.    A 55-year-old man died after being hit by an unidentified vehicle on National Highway 6, near Ranihati in Howrah, on Sunday afternoon. Sambhu Roy, a resident of Panihara in Panchla, was taken to Howrah District Hospital where he was declared dead.    A 35-year-old woman burnt to death in the kitchen of her house in Kamardanga, under Jagachha police station in Howrah, on Saturday afternoon. Babita Das was taken to Howrah District Hospital where she was declared dead. Husband Samar, 40, was arrested after Babitas family lodged a police complaint against him.    An alleged drug-peddler in his late 20s was arrested at the Hazra Road-Kalighat Road crossing on Saturday night. A firearm was found on him. Police said they had received a tip-off that Dipak Ghosh would come to the spot to sell drugs. He has been remanded in police custody till August 19.                                                                                                                                                                
